 The newspaper achieved an outstanding rating according to a Mpumalanga Provincial Survey on companies and institutions doing most in their sectors over the past 12 months to stimulate the economic growth and development of the Mpumalanga Province. The Middelburg Observer was rated by a random, provincial sample of 120 respondents comprising of CEO’s, MD’s, business owners, company directors and managers and senior government officials based in the Mpumlanga Province. It is the fourth consecutive year that the Middelburg Observer has received this award. Read breaking news stories here. Read local news here. Read national news stories here. See videos here.